{
  "texts": [
    "Patent Classification: CPC Classes The CPC system and the IPC (International Patent Classification) system are two of the most commonly used classification systems.",
    "The CPC is a more specific and detailed version of the IPC system.",
    "CPC has a hierarchical structure for classification including Section, Class, Subclass, and Group.",
    "At the Subclass level, CPC has 667 labels (Degroote and Held, 2018).",
    "As shown in Figure 3, in the dataset we had 663 labels that 159 of them have less than 350 samples in the dataset."
  ]
}